This paper deals with optimization problems with sparsity-inducing penalties, which are commonly studied in the field of information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also uses the cavity method, which is a technique commonly used in statistical physics (cs.SI) and applied to optimization problems in computer science. Additionally, the paper deals with the limit of large numbers of variables, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and the analysis of algorithms (cs.DS).
